node.text:
In July 1936, 85 years ago, the Heinkel He 112 V-5 made its first flight. The V-5 appeared from Luftwaffe specifications to make a new fighter, featuring 2 MG's in the nose. However, the V-5 lost the contract and instead some were exported to the Japanese Navy for further tests.

node.text:
On September 18th & 19th, the Italian aerobatic team ‘Frecce Tricolori’ will celebrate its 60th anniversary! The most experienced pilots in the Italian Air Force go through a difficult selection process to join the famous team. More than 20 challenging aerobatics for a half-hour performance are known to many aerobatics fans around the world. The Frecce Tricolori group is one of the national symbols of Italy!

Until 12:00 GMT on the 20th of September, destroy 30/15/15 (AB/RB/SB) enemy aircraft flying the G.91 pre-serie and get the “Frecce Tricolori” camouflage for this aircraft!
_________________________________________

node.text:
80 years ago, the 3" Gun Carrier appeared for the first time. The Gun Carrier was a Churchill, fitted with the 76 mm gun. This gun was put into several existing tanks, and therefore the Gun Carrier was deemed no longer viable, with the 50 built seeing no combat.
_________________________________________

node.text:
Today, 79 years ago, the first prototype of the AS 42 was built. While derived from the AB 41 armored car it ironically had no armor itself. About 200 were built and could be equipped with various main armaments such as anti-aircraft cannons, anti-tank rifles, and machine guns.
_________________________________________
